---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            color: #333;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
        }

        .container {
            width: 80%;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 30px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #fff;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 36px;
            color: #2c3e50;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        p {
            font-size: 18px;
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }

        .intro {
            font-size: 20px;
            color: #555;
            font-weight: bold;
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 28px;
            color: #34495e;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }

        ul, ol {
            margin: 15px 0;
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        code {
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            padding: 5px;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-size: 1.1em;
            color: #c0392b;
        }

        .code-example {
            background-color: #ecf0f1;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin: 15px 0;
            font-family: monospace;
        }

        .highlight {
            color: #e74c3c;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        footer {
            text-align: center;
            margin-top: 30px;
            padding-top: 10px;
            border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
            color: #777;
            font-size: 14px;
        }
    </style>
    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <h1>What is Programming?</h1>
            <p class="intro">Programming is the process of writing instructions that a computer can execute to perform a task.</p>
        </header>

        <section>
            <h2>Understanding the Basics</h2>
            <p>Programming is like giving directions to a computer, telling it step-by-step what to do. These directions are written in <span class="highlight">programming languages</span> that the computer can understand and process.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Why Learn Programming?</h2>
            <p>Learning programming opens up many opportunities. Here are a few reasons to start programming:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>It allows you to create websites, apps, games, and more.</li>
                <li>You can automate repetitive tasks and save time.</li>
                <li>Programming skills are in high demand in the job market.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Common Programming Languages</h2>
            <p>There are several popular programming languages, each with its own unique features. Some of the most commonly used languages include:</p>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Python</strong> - Known for its readability and simplicity. Great for beginners.</li>
                <li><strong>JavaScript</strong> - Primarily used for web development to make websites interactive.</li>
                <li><strong>Java</strong> - A versatile language used in many applications, including Android development.</li>
                <li><strong>C++</strong> - Known for its performance and used in game development and system programming.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Example of a Simple Program</h2>
            <p>Letâ€™s look at an example of a basic <code>Python</code> program that prints "Hello, World!" to the screen:</p>
            <div class="code-example">
                <code>
                    print("Hello, World!")
                </code>
            </div>
            <p>This simple program instructs the computer to display the text "Hello, World!"</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>How Does Programming Work?</h2>
            <p>Programming involves several steps:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Writing code:</strong> The programmer writes code in a programming language.</li>
                <li><strong>Compiling:</strong> The code is translated into a format the computer can understand.</li>
                <li><strong>Executing:</strong> The computer runs the compiled code and performs the tasks instructed by the program.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Key Concepts in Programming</h2>
            <p>Some important concepts every programmer should understand include:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Variables:</strong> Used to store data that the program can manipulate.</li>
                <li><strong>Data types:</strong> The kind of data that can be stored, such as numbers, text, etc.</li>
                <li><strong>Loops:</strong> Repeating a set of instructions multiple times.</li>
                <li><strong>Functions:</strong> A block of code designed to perform a specific task.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <footer>
            <p>&copy; 2024 Learn2Code | Empowering beginners to dive into programming</p>
        </footer>
    </div>
</BaseLayout>